<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer12000543043133786207">Robert &quot;Bob&quot; Upshur Woodward is an assistant managing editor of <i>The Washington Post</i>. While an investigative reporter for that newspaper, Woodward, working with fellow reporter Carl Bernstein, helped uncover the Watergate scandal that led to U.S. President Richard Nixon&apos;s resignation. Woodward has written 12 best-selling non-fiction books and has twice contributed reporting to efforts that collecti</span>
  <span id="freeText12000543043133786207" style="display:none">Robert "Bob" Upshur Woodward is an assistant managing editor of <i>The Washington Post</i>. While an investigative reporter for that newspaper, Woodward, working with fellow reporter Carl Bernstein, helped uncover the Watergate scandal that led to U.S. President Richard Nixon's resignation. Woodward has written 12 best-selling non-fiction books and has twice contributed reporting to efforts that collectively earned the Post and its National Reporting staff a Pulitzer Prize.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12000543043133786207" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

